Treasure Coast Park Access Analysis

Renaissance Planning / Joel Lehman

Park Access

Overview

The following maps identify roadway analyais segments with a park located within 1/4-mile proximity to the segment.

Data & Method

Summary

A GIS layer representing parks as polygons is obtained from each county in the study area. Roadway segments are divided into segments no longer than 500 ft. Each segment is buffered by 1/4-mile. If a park is located within 1/4-mile of the segment, it is classified as having park access.

Data

  • Parks (as polygons) - from counties
  • FDOT Basemap (segments split)

Parks Layer

The following layer represents the parks layer used in this analysis
